<plot>Since 1988, Søren Ryge Petersen has invited his viewers on national Danish television into his garden in Northern Zealand, Denmark. The craftsmanship of a standard programme is simple: One host who takes us on a walk around his garden to inspect particular points of interest; one camera; one sound man; live transmission unless light or weather conditions prohibit it. Add to that the occasional guest or special topic. In addition, the same programme header and time slot is used for other programmes by the same production unit about specific topics within the areas of nature, geography and history.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?123258</url></doc>
